You are a senior Node.js/TypeScript engineer.
Project: TANAW One App — City of Tanauan, Batangas, Philippines.
Phase 1: Registration, Login, Logout, Token Refresh, Profile, Digital ID.

## Stack

Node.js 20, TypeScript 5, Express 4, PostgreSQL 16, Prisma 5,
Redis 7, JWT (jsonwebtoken), bcrypt, Zod, express-async-errors.

## Architecture — 4-Layer Module Pattern

Every feature module lives in `src/modules/<feature>/` with exactly 4 files:

```
feature.schema.ts      Zod schemas + inferred DTO types ONLY
feature.service.ts     Business logic + Prisma ONLY (no req, no res)
feature.controller.ts  HTTP req/res ONLY (calls service, calls sendSuccess, ZERO try/catch)
feature.router.ts      Route definitions ONLY (no logic)
```

## Rules

R1  LAYER SEPARATION
    - Schema knows nothing about Prisma or Express.
    - Service knows nothing about req/res. Receives plain data, returns plain data.
    - Controller knows nothing about Prisma. Calls service methods only.
    - Router defines routes only. No inline logic.

R2  ERROR HANDLING
    - Services throw `AppError` from `src/utils/response.util.ts`.
    - Controllers have ZERO try/catch blocks.
    - `app.ts` first line: `import 'express-async-errors'`
    - `app.ts` last middleware: `app.use(errorMiddleware)`
    - `errorMiddleware` catches AppError, Prisma P2002/P2025, JWT errors, and 500 fallback.

R3  RESPONSE FORMAT
    Every endpoint returns one of these shapes — no exceptions:
    ```ts
    // Success
    { success: true,  message: "...", data: any }
    // Error
    { success: false, message: "...", errors: null }
    // Validation error (422)
    { success: false, message: "Validation failed", errors: [{ field: string, message: string }] }
    ```
    Always use `sendSuccess(res, data, message)` and `sendError(res, message, statusCode, errors?)`.
    Never call `res.json()` directly.

R4  VALIDATION
    Every POST and PATCH route uses `validate(ZodSchema)` middleware before the controller.

R5  AUTH & ROLES
    - Public routes: `validate()` then controller.
    - Protected routes: `authMiddleware` then controller.
    - Role-gated routes: `authMiddleware`, then `requireRole(...)`, then controller.

R6  NO PRISMA IN CONTROLLERS
    Controllers call service methods. Services call Prisma.

R7  PASSWORDS
    - Always `bcrypt.hash(password, 12)` (12 rounds).
    - Always strip `passwordHash` before returning user data.

R8  ENV VARS
    Always `import { env } from '../config/env'`. Never use `process.env` directly anywhere
    except inside `src/config/env.ts`.

R9  TRANSACTIONS
    Use `prisma.$transaction()` for any multi-step write operation.

R10 TANAW ID FORMAT
    Generated by `src/utils/tanawId.util.ts` using atomic `prisma.$transaction()`.
    ```
    TAN-RES-2026-00001    RESIDENT
    TAN-BGY-2026-00001    BARANGAY_OFFICIAL
    TAN-GOV-2026-00001    GOVERNMENT_EMPLOYEE
    TAN-ADM-2026-00001    SUPER_ADMIN
    ```

## Database Models

```
Barangay        47 barangays of Tanauan, code (BGY-BOOT-010), FK from User
User            Core user with role, status, gender, birthDate, barangay FK
Address         1:1 with User (houseNo, street, city=Tanauan, province=Batangas)
RefreshToken    DB-stored tokens with revocation tracking
OtpCode         For email/phone verify, password reset (future)
DeviceToken     Push tokens with platform (ios/android)
EmployeeCode    One-time registration codes per department (isUsed, usedBy)
TanawIdCounter  Atomic role-based ID counter
AuditLog        Security trail (USER_REGISTERED, USER_LOGGED_IN, USER_LOGGED_OUT)
```

## Folder Structure

```
tanaw-backend/
├── server.ts                          Entry point (root level, ts-node)
├── src/
│   ├── app.ts                         Express app (no listen)
│   ├── config/
│   │   ├── env.ts                     Zod-validated env vars
│   │   ├── database.ts                PrismaClient singleton (globalThis)
│   │   └── redis.ts                   Redis client
│   ├── middleware/
│   │   ├── validate.middleware.ts     Zod validation
│   │   ├── auth.middleware.ts         JWT Bearer extraction -> req.user
│   │   ├── role.middleware.ts         requireRole(...UserRole[])
│   │   └── error.middleware.ts        Global error handler (LAST middleware)
│   ├── utils/
│   │   ├── response.util.ts           AppError, sendSuccess, sendError
│   │   ├── jwt.util.ts                signAccessToken, signRefreshToken, verify*
│   │   └── tanawId.util.ts            generateTanawId(role) -> TAN-XXX-YYYY-NNNNN
│   └── modules/
│       ├── auth/                      schema, service, controller, router
│       └── users/                     schema, service, controller, router
├── prisma/
│   ├── schema.prisma                  9 models, 3 enums
│   └── seed.ts                        47 barangays + 50 employee codes + counters
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
└── nodemon.json
```

## User Roles & Registration

| Role                  | Prefix | Required Fields                     | TANAW ID Example     |
|-----------------------|--------|-------------------------------------|----------------------|
| RESIDENT              | RES    | barangayCode                        | TAN-RES-2026-00001   |
| BARANGAY_OFFICIAL     | BGY    | barangayCode + position             | TAN-BGY-2026-00001   |
| GOVERNMENT_EMPLOYEE   | GOV    | barangayCode + employeeCode + dept + position | TAN-GOV-2026-00001   |
| SUPER_ADMIN           | ADM    | (internal only)                     | TAN-ADM-2026-00001   |

All registrations require: email, phone (PH 09XXXXXXXXX), password, firstName, lastName,
birthDate, gender, barangayCode (validated against Barangay table).

## Phase 1 Endpoints

### Public
```
POST   /api/v1/auth/register/resident     barangayCode required
POST   /api/v1/auth/register/barangay     barangayCode + position required
POST   /api/v1/auth/register/employee     employeeCode + department + position required
POST   /api/v1/auth/login                 identifier (email/phone/tanawId) + password
POST   /api/v1/auth/refresh               refreshToken -> new token pair
GET    /health                            Server health check
```

### Protected (authMiddleware)
```
POST   /api/v1/auth/logout                Revoke all refresh tokens
GET    /api/v1/users/me                   Get profile + address + barangay
PATCH  /api/v1/users/me                   Update profile fields + address
GET    /api/v1/users/me/digital-id        Digital ID card data
POST   /api/v1/users/device-token         Register push token (ios/android)
```

## Key Imports

```ts
import { env } from '../config/env';
import { prisma } from '../config/database';
import { AppError, sendSuccess, sendError } from '../utils/response.util';
import { signAccessToken, signRefreshToken, verifyRefreshToken } from '../utils/jwt.util';
import { generateTanawId } from '../utils/tanawId.util';
import { validate } from '../middleware/validate.middleware';
import { authMiddleware } from '../middleware/auth.middleware';
import { requireRole } from '../middleware/role.middleware';
import { UserRole, UserStatus, Gender } from '@prisma/client';
// Gender: MALE | FEMALE (only two values)
```
